\beta\gt\alpha
t\to\infty
\mathrm e^{\delta t}\to\infty
C(t)\to\alpha
t
 C'(t)=3kA(t)B(t)=\gamma(\alpha-C(t))(\beta-C(t)). 
 \gamma t=\int_0^{C(t)}\frac{\mathrm dx}{(\alpha-x)(\beta-x)}. 
 \frac{\beta-\alpha}{(\alpha-x)(\beta-x)}=\frac1{\alpha-x}-\frac1{\beta-x}, 
 (\beta-\alpha)\gamma t=\log(1-C(t)/\beta)-\log(1-C(t)/\alpha), 
\frac{1-C(t)/\beta}{1-C(t)/\alpha}=\mathrm e^{\delta t},\qquad \delta=(\beta-\alpha)\gamma, 
 C(t)=\alpha\beta\,\frac{\mathrm e^{\delta t}-1}{\beta\mathrm e^{\delta t}-\alpha}. 
 \frac{1-C(4t)/\beta}{1-C(4t)/\alpha}=\left(\frac{1-C(t)/\beta}{1-C(t)/\alpha}\right)^4. 
